January 2013, NERC/Centre for Ecology & Hydrology, Lancaster.</dcterms:description>     <dcterms:title xml:lang="en">Distribution of Ash trees in Countryside Survey</dcterms:title>     <dcterms:creator>clamw</dcterms:creator>     <dcterms:isPartOf>       <documentcontainer:documentContainer rdf:about="http://eidchub.ceh.ac.uk/metadata/05e5d538-6be7-476d-9141-76d9328738a4">         <dcterms:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2013-08-20T10:19:43Z</dcterms:created>         <dcterms:description xml:lang="en">The dataset consists of a distribution map of ash trees (Fraxinus excelsior) within woody linear features across Great Britain.  The data is derived from Countryside Survey 2007 and includes trees recorded in lines of trees of a natural shape and lines of trees of an unnatural shape.  Trees were mapped in 569 1km sample squares across Britain, and this national estimate dataset was derived from the sample data using ITE Land Classes.</dcterms:description>         <dcterms:title
